parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Shifter Assembly Failure (Shift to Park Issue)
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shifter assembly can cause the vehicle to not recognize that it is in park, leading to safety concerns such as the vehicle rolling forward or backward, and the inability to turn off the engine, which can cause carbon monoxide poisoning or other hazards.
symptoms: The "Shift to Park" warning message is displayed on the dashboard
the vehicle does not recognize that it is in park
the engine does not turn off
the interior lights stay on
and the vehicle cannot be locked.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slippage and hesitation can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or stalling, which can cause safety risks to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The vehicle shudders
hesitates
or surges forward when accelerating
the transmission slips
and the vehicle downshifts unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the timing chain and camshaft can cause the engine to malfunction, leading to stalling or loss of power, which can cause safety risks to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The engine stalls
the check engine warning light is illuminated
and the vehicle experiences loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to recognize the vehicle is in park can cause the vehicle to remain running, leading to battery drain, and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The "Shift to Park" error message appears on the dashboard
the vehicle fails to turn off
the battery drains
and the vehicle may roll.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Side Blind Zone Alert Module Water Intrusion
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion into the Side Blind Zone Alert module can cause electrical system malfunctions, leading to loss of driver interface functions, and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The "Service Side Detection" error message appears on the dashboard
the side blind zone alert message is displayed
and the system may malfunction or fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission systems can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle stalls or fails to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system malfunctions can cause a range of issues, including failure of the parking brake, door locks, and other systems, leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: The parking brake engages randomly
the door locks malfunction
and other electrical systems fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water leaks into the electrical system can cause a range of issues, including electrical system malfunctions, leading to safety concerns.
symptoms: Water leaks into the electrical system
causing electrical system malfunctions
and potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to recognize the vehicle is in park can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The dashboard displays "Shift to Park" or "Action Required" messages
even when the vehicle is already in park. The vehicle may not shut off
and the parking lights
radio
and accessories may remain on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the side detection module can cause the vehicle to die or stall, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The side detection alarm beeps randomly
and the dashboard displays "Service Side Detection Module Failure" warnings.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hood latch can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The dashboard displays "Theft Warning" and "Hood Open" warnings
and the vehicle may not auto-start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The difficulty in pushing the horn can cause a delay in warning other drivers of a potential hazard, leading to accidents.
symptoms: The horn is hard to push and requires both hands to activate.
